Enum RouteOptions.TransportMode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<RouteOptions.TransportMode>
      • com.here.android.mpa.routing.RouteOptions.TransportMode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<RouteOptions.TransportMode>
    Enclosing class:
    RouteOptions

    public static enum RouteOptions.TransportMode
extends java.lang.Enum<RouteOptions.TransportMode>
    Represents values describing different mode of transportation a person will be using. (for example, Car, or Public Transit).

      • PUBLIC_TRANSPORT

        @Deprecated
public static final RouteOptions.TransportMode PUBLIC_TRANSPORT
        Deprecated. As of SDK 3.2. Use UMRouter with UMRouteOptions.
        Public transport is being used as the mode of transportation.

        Note: a transit route may not be found if the walking distance from the start to the first transit station, or from the final transit station to the end, is greater than 3 kilometers.

        To use this feature, your application must include the google-gson library (release 2.2.4 or a compatible version) on its class path. This library can be downloaded from the google-gson project website at http://code.google.com/p/google-gson/. Attempting to use this feature without adding this library will cause runtime errors.

      • TRACK

        public static final RouteOptions.TransportMode TRACK
        Straight line connecting the waypoints of a route. As of 3.2.2, TRACK mode is no longer supported and a route will not be calculated if using this mode. Please see RouteManager.calculateRoute(RoutePlan,RouteManager.Listener) and CoreRouter.calculateRoute(RoutePlan, Listener) for more information.
